parameters:
\n<Ameria>"There's a barrier in place so monsters can't come and go as
they please! If you do that, you'll get hurt--ah, see,
you've burned your arm!"

\n<Lyric>"You're the one who did this, what are you even saying!
Damn... let go, don't touch me!"

\n<Lyric>"Enough already! How long do you plan to keep me locked up
in this place?!"
\n<Ameria>"But... my sister said not to let you out..."

\n<Lyric>"Someone's after me, right? But that doesn't mean I want to
listen to some stranger!"

\n<Ameria>"She's not a stranger, she's my sister! If sister says no,
then you can't go outside!"
\n<Lyric>"So what? Are you stupid or something?!"

\n<Lyric>"...For what it's worth, I'm grateful to you. It seems you
took care of me while I was dead, and you even fed me."

\n<Lyric>"But that doesn't mean I have to listen to you. I'm a demon.
I don't want to be in a church for even a second."
\n<Lyric>"...This is my final warning. Release the barrier."
Lyric grabbed Ameria by the collar.
\n<Lyric>"I could kill you and break the barrier, you know?"
\n<Ameria>"No... no! I won't let you out...!"
\n<Lyric>"You... then I'll just have to kill you as you wish!"
Lyric released his grip on Ameria's collar.
\n<Ameria>"Lyric... let me see where you got burned..."

\n<Lyric>"Shut up! Don't bother with me! I don't want you to look at
it!"
